e xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qmx1665702737156.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qmx1665702737156.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qmx1665702737156.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qmx1665702737156\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Meta Dictionary\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__meta_dictionary_129999\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The meta dictionary consists of modeled entities that describe the Uniface Repository itself. It is delivered as a file called <span class=\"ph filepath\">umeta.xml</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface/misc</span> directory of your installation. This file also includes some other database tables used by Uniface at runtime.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__note_w4514ab1b5b3_w4515ab1b5_w4516ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> To protect the contents of the Repository, every component that accesses\n         entities of the Repository should have its <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Access</span> property set\n         to <code class=\"ph codeph\">L</code>(Read-Only). This ensures that the information in the Repository\n         cannot be accidentally changed.</div>\n<div class=\"note important note_important\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__note_w4517ab1b5b5_w4518ab1b5_w4519ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Important:</span> If you choose to update the Repository with your own components, you can easily corrupt your definitions so that they can no longer be used by the Uniface compiler. Uniface accepts no responsibility for the contents of the Repository if you choose to update it with your own components.</div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Modeled Entities in the Meta Dictionary</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__1\">\n Model Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__2\">\n Contents\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__3\">\n Default Path\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nuv1665702737229.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nuv1665702737229.html\" title=\"The modeled entities that share the DICT suffix contain the source definitions for your applications. Applications that access DICT entities, primarily the Uniface IDE, locate the associated tables or files on the path $IDF.\">*.DICT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__2\">\n Entities required by the Uniface IDE. For more information, see the documentation for each entity in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">umeta.xml</span> file.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__3\">\n $IDF\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmk1665702737467.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmk1665702737467.html\" title=\"The PRATT.PRINTER entity contains contains the definitions for your print job models. Each occurrence is identified by the name of the model. All applications, except those which never print, access the table or file associated with PRATT.PRINTER on the path $SYS.\">PRATT.PRINTER</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__2\">\n Entity for print job models.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__3\">\n $SYS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"poz1665702737540.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/poz1665702737540.html\" title=\"The USTATE.STATE entity holds state information maintained by the USYSSTAT component for web applications.\">USTATE.STATE</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__2\">\n Entity used to maintain state for web components.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__3\">\n $SYS\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kez1665702737615.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kez1665702737615.html\" title=\"The UOBJ.TEXT entity stores runtime counters that can be addressed using the numgen and numset ProcScript statements. The associated table is usually created at runtime.\">UOBJ.TEXT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__2\">\n Entity used by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numgen</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numget</span> ProcScript statements to store runtime counter names and values.\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qmx1665702737156__table_d4067e1_d4068e1_d4069e1__entry__3\">\n $UUU\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531340\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531340\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Meta Dictionary Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Meta Dictionary The meta dictionary consists of modeled entities that describe the Uniface Repository itself. It is delivered as a file called umeta.xml in the uniface/misc directory of your installation. This file also includes some other database tables used by Uniface at runtime. CAUTION: To protect the contents of the Repository, every component that accesses entities of the Repository should have its Data Access property set to L (Read-Only). This ensures that the information in the Repository cannot be accidentally changed. Important: If you choose to update the Repository with your own components, you can easily corrupt your definitions so that they can no longer be used by the Uniface compiler. Uniface accepts no responsibility for the contents of the Repository if you choose to update it with your own components. Table 1. Modeled Entities in the Meta Dictionary Model Name Contents Default Path *.DICT Entities required by the Uniface IDE. For more information, see the documentation for each entity in the umeta.xml file. $IDF PRATT.PRINTER Entity for print job models. $SYS USTATE.STATE Entity used to maintain state for web components. $SYS UOBJ.TEXT Entity used by the numgen and numget ProcScript statements to store runtime counter names and values. $UUU Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}